  "prompt": "What is the difference between kenyon gyro and 3 axis gimbal? Which gives better stability?",
  "response": "Let me explain the differences between Kenyon Gyro and 3-Axis Gimbal:\n\nKenyon Gyro:\n1. Uses mechanical gyroscopic stabilization\n2. Provides stabilization through spinning weights\n3. Works in multiple axes simultaneously\n4. Typically used in professional video and film production\n5. Heavier and more expensive\n6. Excellent for high-end professional applications\n7. Better for extreme motion and challenging environments\n\n3-Axis Gimbal:\n1. Uses electronic motors and sensors\n2. Stabilizes camera along pitch, roll, and yaw axes\n3. More lightweight and compact\n4. More affordable and versatile\n5. Popular in consumer and prosumer videography\n6. Good for moderate motion stabilization\n7. Works well with smaller cameras and action cameras\n\nStability Comparison:\n- Kenyon Gyro generally provides superior stability\n- Better at handling extreme motion and vibrations\n- More precise and consistent stabilization\n- More expensive and complex\n\n3-Axis Gimbal:\n- Good stability for most typical shooting conditions\n- More accessible and user-friendly\n- Suitable for most amateur and professional video work\n\nChoice depends on specific requirements, budget, and intended use.",
